anemias 280.1 - 281.9, 285.21 - 285.29, 285.9", "bbox": [60.1, 459.7, 366.0, 470.7]}, {"text": "Alcohol abuse 291.0 - 291.3, 291.5, 291.8, 291.81, 291.82, 291.89, 291.9, 303.00 - 303.93, 305.00 - 305.03", "bbox": [60.1, 487.1, 634.8, 498.0]}, {"text": "Drug abuse 292.0, 292.82 - 292.89, 292.9, 304.00 - 304.93, 305.20 - 305.93, 648.30 - 648.34", "bbox": [60.1, 514.4, 578.2, 525.4]}, {"text": "Psychosis 295.00 - 298.9, 299.10, 299.11", "bbox": [60.1, 541.8, 334.4, 552.8]}, {"text": "Depression 300.4, 301.12, 309.0, 309.1, 311", "bbox": [60.1, 569.2, 342.3, 580.1]}, {"text": "TABLE 1: International Classification of Disease, Ninth Clinical Modification (ICD-9-", "bbox": [53.7, 617.8, 628.5, 634.1]}, {"text": "CM) Codes Used to Identify Comorbidities of Bulimia Nervosa", "bbox": [53.7, 639.7, 481.5, 656.0]}, {"text": "Approaches", "bbox": [200.6, 699.5, 289.8, 715.0]}, {"text": "We used the Statistical Package for the Social Science (SPSS), version 23.0 (IBM SPSS Statistics,", "bbox": [200.6, 725.5, 661.7, 736.4]}, {"text": "Armonk, NY) to conduct a retrospective analysis over the HCUP-NIS database from 2010–2014", "bbox": [200.6, 741.0, 659.4, 751.9]}, {"text": "[11]. Descriptive statistics were used to summarize the results. The mean and standard", "bbox": [200.6, 756.5, 620.0, 767.4]}, {"text": "deviations were used to explain the continuous variables. Pearson’s chi-square test and", "bbox": [200.6, 772.0, 624.3, 782.9]}, {"text": "independent sample T-test were used for categorical data and continuous data, respectively. On", "bbox": [200.6, 787.5, 664.8, 798.5]}, {"text": "the other hand, the categorical variables were presented in percentage (%) values. We used a", "bbox": [200.6, 803.0, 648.3, 814.0]}, {"text": "multinomial logistic regression model to quantify associations among comorbidities and", "bbox": [200.6, 818.5, 629.9, 829.5]}, {"text": "gender (odds ratio (OR); 95% confidence interval (CI)), and the inpatient length of stay (OR;", "bbox": [200.6, 834.0, 646.5, 845.0]}, {"text": "95% CI). We applied the discharge weight, which was given in the NIS database to attain", "bbox": [200.6, 849.5, 627.2, 860.5]}, {"text": "national representation of the inpatient data. A p-value < 0.05 was used as a reference to", "bbox": [200.6, 865.0, 630.7, 876.0]}, {"text": "determine the statistical significance test result.", "bbox": [200.6, 880.5, 435.1, 891.5]}, {"text": "2018 Patel et al. Cureus 10(5): e2583. DOI 10.7759/cureus.2583 4 of 13", "bbox": [33.6, 943.2, 672.3, 954.4]}]}